If there is an &lsquo;A&rsquo;
&lsquo;Not-A&rsquo; appears
Then there must be a &lsquo;B&rsquo; who is observing &lsquo;A&rsquo;
&lsquo;Not-B&rsquo; appears
And then appears a ‘C’ who is observing &lsquo;B&rsquo;
If &lsquo;C&rsquo; is &lsquo;A&rsquo;
Then &lsquo;A&rsquo; and &lsquo;B&rsquo; are observing each other
&lsquo;B&rsquo; must belong to &lsquo;Not-A&rsquo;
&lsquo;A&rsquo; must belong to &lsquo;Not-B&rsquo;
In summary
If there is no &lsquo;A&rsquo;
Then no &lsquo;Not-A&rsquo;
Then no &lsquo;B&rsquo;
Then no &lsquo;Not-B&rsquo;
So launched:
If there is an &lsquo;A&rsquo;, there is an &lsquo;B&rsquo;

We are losing at any time
Because when we are not lost
We are losing &ldquo;lost&rdquo;
